1
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:21,667
The Celeste that you will see
today...

2
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,300
is really different.

3
00:00:24,367 --> 00:00:27,600
I think she no longer wants to
be friends with people like us.

4
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:31,267
You just can't change
your whole personality.

5
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:35,600
Sometimes the real us
is just hidden

6
00:00:35,700 --> 00:00:39,100
by the personality that we want
other people to see.

7
00:00:39,167 --> 00:00:43,133
Maybe Celeste just
forgot her old self.

8
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:45,967
Maybe we can remind her again.

9
00:00:46,033 --> 00:00:48,300
Are you sure about
what you're doing?

10
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:51,933
It seems like it's hard
to get rid of the resentment

11
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:53,300
that was kept for a long time.

12
00:00:53,367 --> 00:00:57,133
So even in my own little way,
I can bring back

13
00:00:57,200 --> 00:01:01,133
even a bit of her respect
for you as her father.

14
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,667
I...

15
00:01:02,733 --> 00:01:08,400
I felt like I was so over you.

16
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:10,500
But...

17
00:01:10,567 --> 00:01:12,933
you told everyone...

18
00:01:16,033 --> 00:01:20,200
that you will marry that woman.

19
00:01:20,267 --> 00:01:22,367
My heart was broken.

20
00:01:22,433 --> 00:01:24,667
I was hoping that we...

21
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,100
will get back together.

22
00:01:29,167 --> 00:01:31,633
Can we be a couple again?

23
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,100
Didn't I tell you that I don't
want to hear anything about her?

24
00:01:37,167 --> 00:01:38,433
Why are you so stubborn?

25
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:41,933
Actually, Tiffany, I didn't
search for your stepmother.

26
00:01:42,033 --> 00:01:44,800
I was searching for alternative
places for our project.

27
00:01:44,867 --> 00:01:46,967
I just found Sorsogon
and there she was.

28
00:01:47,033 --> 00:01:48,867
Sorsogon it is!

29
00:01:48,933 --> 00:01:52,800
Just think that you stepped on
melted grated coconut meat.

30
00:01:52,867 --> 00:01:54,900
Don't try to find out what
it is because it's gross.

31
00:01:54,967 --> 00:01:56,100
Dung?

32
00:01:56,167 --> 00:01:56,933
What happened here?
Why is it so dirty?

33
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,933
Sadly irresponsible tourists.

34
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,433
What a pity, What they did
is not right.

35
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:04,567
It's beautiful here and they
made it dirty like this.

36
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:07,367
Where is my community service?
What will I do?

37
00:02:07,433 --> 00:02:08,233
Isn't it obvious?

38
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:10,333
- I will clean it all?
- Yeah.

39
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,733
You will pick up everything.

40
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:12,767
Hello.

41
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:14,533
Do you want to earn money?

42
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:16,233
You are violating your
community service.

43
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:18,067
You should be the one
doing this.

44
00:02:18,133 --> 00:02:21,167
I'm just teaching them
to segregate and recycle.

45
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:22,800
And they will have a prize.

46
00:02:22,867 --> 00:02:24,267
I'll call Mayor.

47
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:25,467
Look, I'm sorry.

48
00:02:25,533 --> 00:02:28,033
I didn't follow my community
service guidelines.

49
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:29,167
And I'm sorry,

50
00:02:29,233 --> 00:02:32,967
if I made them look like
they're working for me.

51
00:02:33,033 --> 00:02:35,167
Actually, I'm the one who
should apologize to you.

52
00:02:35,233 --> 00:02:37,133
Your idea is good.

53
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:39,267
I called Mayor.

54
00:02:39,333 --> 00:02:42,100
I told him if we can
implement your ideas.

55
00:02:42,167 --> 00:02:44,433
It will help a lot to the waste
management of our area.

56
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:46,200
So congrats, good job.

57
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:56,433
Thank you.

58
00:02:59,033 --> 00:03:01,200
You know...

59
00:03:01,267 --> 00:03:02,600
I'm just trying to do my best.

60
00:03:07,233 --> 00:03:08,933
So I can you know,

61
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,300
get it over and done with.

62
00:03:10,367 --> 00:03:12,067
And then move on with my life.

63
00:03:12,133 --> 00:03:15,433
Get out of here and go back
to my life as a designer...

64
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:18,333
and...

65
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,867
my life with Tonito.

66
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:21,000
So...

67
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:26,233
Yeah, that's my job.

68
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:30,667
Help you to finish your
community service quickly

69
00:03:30,733 --> 00:03:32,667
so you can go back to
the life that you want.

70
00:03:34,633 --> 00:03:35,500
I'll see you tomorrow.
Yeah.

71
00:03:38,467 --> 00:03:39,500
Okay.

72
00:03:39,567 --> 00:03:40,267
Bye.

73
00:04:20,833 --> 00:04:21,933
Tonito?

74
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:27,300
Finally, you're awake.

75
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,333
What time is it?

76
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:30,367
It's already afternoon.

77
00:04:31,533 --> 00:04:33,167
I'm so sorry.

78
00:04:33,233 --> 00:04:35,800
It looked like I drank a lot
last night.

79
00:04:35,867 --> 00:04:37,200
You should be thankful
to the maid.

80
00:04:37,267 --> 00:04:39,167
She took care of you.

81
00:04:39,233 --> 00:04:41,100
Did I bother you?

82
00:04:41,167 --> 00:04:42,867
Did I say something bad?

83
00:04:44,233 --> 00:04:48,933
Nothing because you passed out
when you arrived.

84
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,833
I thought I said something
that I will regret

85
00:04:51,900 --> 00:04:53,233
for the rest of my life.

86
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:56,967
I'll go ahead.

87
00:05:00,033 --> 00:05:01,000
Mom?

88
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,033
Hi, Tiff.

89
00:05:45,567 --> 00:05:46,733
Yes, we are waiting for her.

90
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,267
Hey, it's Celeste.

91
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:49,767
Mother, Father.

92
00:05:55,867 --> 00:05:57,567
What happened?

93
00:05:57,633 --> 00:05:59,500
Your father and I are talking

94
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:02,967
about expanding
our Pili nut business.

95
00:06:04,433 --> 00:06:08,967
Celeste, your Auntie Adora
is running our business well

96
00:06:09,067 --> 00:06:10,467
in the Pili farm.

97
00:06:10,533 --> 00:06:15,200
As time goes on, the business
is doing good.

98
00:06:15,267 --> 00:06:17,967
And what's even better
is that your Auntie Adora

99
00:06:18,033 --> 00:06:20,900
saved your shares
in our pili farm.

100
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:22,800
That's why we have big savings

101
00:06:22,867 --> 00:06:25,567
because your shares
were put aside.

102
00:06:25,633 --> 00:06:30,133
We thought that maybe we can use
your money for investment

103
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:32,833
to open up branches in Albay.

104
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:34,200
With the big money
that was saved,

105
00:06:34,267 --> 00:06:38,567
we can even open in Farmers
Market in Cubao.

106
00:06:38,633 --> 00:06:42,200
Our Pili nuts will be more
saleable in Manila.

107
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:43,667
Celeste, just think about it.

108
00:06:43,733 --> 00:06:47,000
If we have a branch where
we can sell our products,

109
00:06:47,067 --> 00:06:51,467
people from Manila will no
longer have to come here

110
00:06:51,533 --> 00:06:55,233
just to taste an authentic
Pili nut.

111
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:57,400
Have I not made myself clear?

112
00:06:57,467 --> 00:07:00,900
I never intended to stay
here in Sorsogon.

113
00:07:00,967 --> 00:07:03,700
I don't want to get involved
in that Pili nut business.

114
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:07,600
With the same logic that
I have a life in Manila.

115
00:07:07,667 --> 00:07:08,733
I'm a fashion designer there.

116
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:10,800
I have so much on my plate.

117
00:07:10,867 --> 00:07:12,600
I have no time for this.

118
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:13,933
My life is there.

119
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,767
So anything under my name,

120
00:07:16,867 --> 00:07:18,133
you can do whatever you want
with it.

121
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,900
Even if you feed
that to whale shark,

122
00:07:19,967 --> 00:07:21,767
I don't care.

123
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:22,967
You are stubborn.

124
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:29,700
Celeste is really arrogant.

125
00:07:29,767 --> 00:07:30,633
Sebastian!

126
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,400
I know what you're thinking.

127
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:51,933
Nothing happened to me
and your Mom.

128
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:55,167
She got drunk,
that's why she slept here.

129
00:07:55,233 --> 00:07:58,500
Dad, chill. Why are you
so defensive?

130
00:07:58,567 --> 00:08:00,933
I'm not asking.

131
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:03,233
It would be better
if it's clear to you.

132
00:08:04,867 --> 00:08:07,767
Yeah, I know
that you have Celeste.

133
00:08:08,767 --> 00:08:10,933
Tiff, stop being sarcastic.

134
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,367
I am not.

135
00:08:14,033 --> 00:08:18,467
Fine, I'm starting to wonder
when you will talk to me again

136
00:08:18,533 --> 00:08:22,433
after you walked out
the last time we had lunch.

137
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,100
Do you realize your mistake?

138
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,967
Dad, let's not go there anymore.

139
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:38,333
So, what do you want?

140
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:41,167
Say it, because I don't want
to be late for the event

141
00:08:41,233 --> 00:08:43,567
that our company-sponsored.

142
00:08:44,967 --> 00:08:46,767
Well, I'm going out of town.

143
00:08:48,267 --> 00:08:50,033
What for?

144
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:52,600
For my school project.

145
00:08:52,667 --> 00:08:54,433
We will go to Sorsogon.

146
00:08:56,867 --> 00:09:01,733
Well, you do know that your
Auntie Celeste is there.

147
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:04,233
Of course, I know, Dad.

148
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:08,467
Celeste made a mess in Sorsogon
and it's all over the place.

149
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:11,500
But Dad, this project has
nothing to do with her.

150
00:09:11,567 --> 00:09:12,833
It's just a coincidence

151
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:16,100
that's where we want to go,
where she's making a mess.

152
00:09:16,167 --> 00:09:18,400
I've been watching
her videos lately

153
00:09:18,467 --> 00:09:21,600
and she seems to be doing
pretty well.

154
00:09:21,667 --> 00:09:25,133
She spearheaded the waste
management program in an area

155
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,567
to mitigate global warming.

156
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:32,400
So if there's one person
who can help in Sorsogon

157
00:09:32,467 --> 00:09:34,400
that would be
your Auntie Celeste.

158
00:09:34,467 --> 00:09:36,233
She grew up there

159
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:39,900
and she knows the place
like the back of her hand.

160
00:09:39,967 --> 00:09:44,833
Dad, I'll be going there with
my friends and my schoolmates.

161
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:47,333
What will I tell them?

162
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:50,467
Guys, this is my Dad's
other woman.

163
00:09:51,867 --> 00:09:54,767
She ruined my family.

164
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:56,400
Don't start again, Tiff.

165
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,300
Okay, Dad...

166
00:10:03,467 --> 00:10:06,533
I did not come here to fight.

167
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:11,067
I was just being polite
to ask for your permission

168
00:10:11,133 --> 00:10:13,767
because after all,
you are my father.

169
00:10:13,833 --> 00:10:16,200
And you deserve to know
where I'm going

170
00:10:16,267 --> 00:10:18,167
and what I will do there.

171
00:10:18,233 --> 00:10:20,867
But please, Dad, please...

172
00:10:22,067 --> 00:10:24,333
the last thing that I want
to happen there

173
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,633
is to mingle
with your girlfriend.

174
00:10:30,467 --> 00:10:31,833
Excuse me.

175
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:32,900
Good night, Dad.

176
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,467
So, I'm going to finish
all the sketches now,

177
00:10:44,533 --> 00:10:47,100
and then, I'll email this
to you.

178
00:10:47,167 --> 00:10:48,800
You can produce the samples,

179
00:10:48,867 --> 00:10:51,033
so you can release it
to the public, okay?

180
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:54,700
Perfect and your engagement
is getting stronger

181
00:10:54,767 --> 00:10:57,633
because we uploaded your
activities in Sorsogon.

182
00:10:57,700 --> 00:11:02,033
We can sustain our increase
in sales with our new designs.

183
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:05,333
Wonderful, so just wait
for my email.

184
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,967
I'll just finish
all my sketches now.

185
00:11:08,067 --> 00:11:10,567
Okay, happy drawing.

186
00:11:10,633 --> 00:11:11,700
Okay, thank you.

187
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:27,733
Actually, your idea is good.

188
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,767
I called Mayor.

189
00:11:29,833 --> 00:11:32,600
I told him if we can implement
your ideas.

190
00:11:32,667 --> 00:11:36,900
You know, encourage recycling,
waste segregation.

191
00:11:36,967 --> 00:11:40,033
It will help a lot to the waste
management in our area.

192
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:41,833
So...

193
00:11:41,933 --> 00:11:43,833
congrats, good job.

194
00:11:45,867 --> 00:11:47,000
You did a good job.

195
00:11:47,067 --> 00:11:49,167
Congratulations on a job
well done.

196
00:11:49,233 --> 00:11:50,767
Ugh...

197
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:51,967
oh my God.

198
00:11:52,033 --> 00:11:55,633
He thought he can get me
with his cute and charming ways.

199
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:56,967
No way.

200
00:12:10,667 --> 00:12:13,033
I'm just trying to do my best.

201
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:16,200
So I can, you know,
get it over and done with.

202
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,067
Move on with my life.

203
00:12:18,133 --> 00:12:22,200
Get out of here and go back
to my life as a designer.

204
00:12:22,267 --> 00:12:26,267
Yeah, and my life with Tonito.

205
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:29,300
She thought she really
has a good life in Manila.

206
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,967
What is he doing?
Why is he calling me?

207
00:12:54,033 --> 00:12:55,367
Hello, it's already late.

208
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:56,600
Hello?

209
00:12:58,333 --> 00:12:59,667
Hello...

210
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:00,967
I just want to tell you

211
00:13:01,033 --> 00:13:03,600
that there will be a change in
your community service tomorrow.

212
00:13:03,667 --> 00:13:06,500
It'll be earlier because
where we are going is far.

213
00:13:06,567 --> 00:13:11,100
So prepare yourself because you
will have a long day tomorrow.

214
00:13:11,167 --> 00:13:12,867
Okay.

215
00:13:12,933 --> 00:13:16,633
You should be excited because
if you have a long day tomorrow

216
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:20,467
that means your community
service will be faster.

217
00:13:20,533 --> 00:13:21,967
That's what you want, right?

218
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:26,733
For it to end so you can back to
your beautiful life in Manila.

219
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:27,900
And just like you,

220
00:13:27,967 --> 00:13:32,867
I can also go back to what I do
that's more important.

221
00:13:32,933 --> 00:13:34,500
Okay, great.

222
00:13:34,567 --> 00:13:37,467
So don't call me anymore
because I have to go to sleep.

223
00:13:37,533 --> 00:13:38,400
It's already late.

224
00:13:38,467 --> 00:13:40,100
We have to be early tomorrow,
right?

225
00:13:40,167 --> 00:13:41,700
Fabulous, bye.

226
00:13:46,833 --> 00:13:48,367
She's so fussy.

227
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:53,200
What is that?

228
00:13:53,267 --> 00:13:54,600
So I can carry on with my life.

229
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,333
What will you do here?

230
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,400
You're so busy here in Sorsogon?

231
00:13:58,467 --> 00:14:00,400
Watching the sunrise
and the sunset.

232
00:14:01,367 --> 00:14:05,267
His sense of self-importance
is very inflated.

233
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:09,133
Oh my God, he's calling again.

234
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:11,367
Hello, what's with you?

235
00:14:11,433 --> 00:14:13,100
Don't you think it's a little
unethical for you

236
00:14:13,167 --> 00:14:15,467
to call me so late at night?

237
00:14:15,533 --> 00:14:17,867
Love, did I catch you
at a bad time?

238
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:25,333
Tonito?

239
00:14:29,967 --> 00:14:32,133
Love, did I catch you
at a bad time?

240
00:14:33,267 --> 00:14:35,433
Tonito?

241
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,733
I just want to check on you.

242
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:38,633
I wasn't able to call you

243
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:40,500
because my schedule today
is full.

244
00:14:40,567 --> 00:14:43,067
I wanted to call you earlier,

245
00:14:43,133 --> 00:14:46,167
but I was stuck
in a formal event.

246
00:14:46,233 --> 00:14:47,700
Sorry, Love.

247
00:14:47,767 --> 00:14:49,067
I was so annoyed.

248
00:14:49,133 --> 00:14:53,267
Someone keeps on calling me
about the schedule change.

249
00:14:53,333 --> 00:14:54,167
Who?

250
00:14:56,833 --> 00:15:01,400
The one who handles
my community service.

251
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,033
There is a change
in my community service

252
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:03,933
and all of that.

253
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,567
So...

254
00:15:05,633 --> 00:15:07,033
Can they do that?

255
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:09,733
Well I guess, because the
officer reports to the court

256
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:13,833
If I'm doing my part
in the community service.

257
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:16,200
Well in that case, if you need
to be early tomorrow,

258
00:15:16,267 --> 00:15:18,000
I won't keep you up.

259
00:15:18,067 --> 00:15:20,867
I just called because I wanted
to inform you

260
00:15:20,933 --> 00:15:23,633
that Tiffany is going
to Sorsogon.

261
00:15:23,700 --> 00:15:28,133
She's doing a school project
there and I was thinking

262
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,767
if you can and maybe you have
the time,

263
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:33,100
maybe you can help her.

264
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:35,933
And I think that this is a good
opportunity for the two of you

265
00:15:36,033 --> 00:15:38,567
to become close.

266
00:15:38,633 --> 00:15:41,167
Wow, that's great.

267
00:15:41,233 --> 00:15:43,033
I just hope that she wants
to see me too

268
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:47,067
because I'm not her most
favorite person in the world.

269
00:15:50,367 --> 00:15:52,233
Maybe you're right.

270
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:55,767
She might get mad, if I keep
on pushing you two together.

271
00:15:57,633 --> 00:15:59,833
Well, I miss you.

272
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:06,533
I miss my very supportive
and appreciative fiancé.

273
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:08,367
I miss you too.

274
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:09,967
And don't worry,

275
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:14,167
once you're mine, you will never
get out of my sight.

276
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:18,033
Okay?

277
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:19,633
Go and sleep early, Love.

278
00:16:19,700 --> 00:16:21,233
I love you. Good night.

279
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:50,867
Sketch.

280
00:17:27,567 --> 00:17:28,667
You should get some sleep.

281
00:17:30,133 --> 00:17:33,500
I'm sure in a couple of hours
we'll be in Bicol.

282
00:17:34,867 --> 00:17:36,933
Come on, James. I know you.

283
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,033
For sure you will fall asleep.

284
00:17:39,100 --> 00:17:42,067
So I'll be more comfortable
and awake just to make sure

285
00:17:42,133 --> 00:17:45,467
that you will not fall asleep
while driving.

286
00:17:45,533 --> 00:17:50,467
Okay and in a while it's
morning, so I'm okay.

287
00:17:50,567 --> 00:17:53,267
You never trust me, do you?

288
00:17:56,667 --> 00:17:58,733
Just be careful James, okay?

289
00:18:00,067 --> 00:18:03,367
Tiffany, if you are the brain
of the script,

290
00:18:03,433 --> 00:18:05,433
I'm the transport.

291
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:08,400
So can you stop worrying, okay?

292
00:18:08,467 --> 00:18:10,967
Okay.

293
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:23,033
Someone texted you.

294
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:30,600
It's your ex.

295
00:18:30,667 --> 00:18:32,767
Why is she texting at this hour?

296
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:34,400
- What are you talking about?
- Give me the phone.

297
00:18:34,467 --> 00:18:35,533
- Oh my gosh...
- Tiffany...

298
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:37,300
- you two are talking again.
- give me the phone.

299
00:18:37,367 --> 00:18:38,200
- Tiffany!
- Stop the car!
Stop the car!

300
00:18:39,267 --> 00:18:40,233
What's with you?

301
00:18:41,633 --> 00:18:42,733
Give me the phone.

302
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:43,733
Okay, fine.

303
00:18:44,933 --> 00:18:47,033
- You keep on doing this, James.
- What are you doing?

304
00:18:47,100 --> 00:18:47,967
I will leave.

305
00:18:48,033 --> 00:18:49,067
- In this?
- Yeah.

306
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:50,233
It's dark.

307
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:52,233
You're a girl. You're in the
middle of nowhere.

308
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:53,133
Do you really think
- you can go and leave?
- And so?

309
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,433
Go, I dare you.

310
00:18:55,533 --> 00:18:56,867
- Do you think I can't?
- I don't think you can do it.

311
00:18:56,933 --> 00:18:57,900
Do you think I can't do it?

312
00:18:57,967 --> 00:18:59,200
I don't think you can.

313
00:18:59,267 --> 00:19:01,533
You always come back.

314
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:07,400
Tiff?

315
00:19:08,767 --> 00:19:09,533
Tiff.

316
00:19:11,433 --> 00:19:12,267
Tiff.

317
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:15,100
Tiff...

318
00:19:15,167 --> 00:19:15,867
Don't do this.

319
00:19:15,933 --> 00:19:17,400
Come on. Get back in the car.

320
00:19:17,467 --> 00:19:19,433
- Don't do this.
- Don't touch me.

321
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:20,200
What?

322
00:19:20,267 --> 00:19:21,567
And you too, Clau. Leave.

323
00:19:23,033 --> 00:19:24,100
I want to be alone.

324
00:19:25,367 --> 00:19:26,333
Leave!

325
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,633
Fine.

326
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:29,133
Clau, let's go.

327
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:31,333
Tiff?

328
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:32,300
Clau!

329
00:19:46,233 --> 00:19:47,333
Wow!

330
00:19:57,067 --> 00:19:58,567
Oh my God!

331
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:04,000
I hate you!

332
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:24,000
I wonder what's going on

333
00:20:24,067 --> 00:20:28,133
in Celeste and Mikoy's
community service?

334
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,333
I don't know Grandmother Ikay.

335
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:33,833
But I already asked
the crystal ball.

336
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:38,867
It says the two are still
like cat and dog.

337
00:20:38,967 --> 00:20:41,000
That's only in the beginning.

338
00:20:41,067 --> 00:20:44,633
I knew those two very well
since they were kids.

339
00:20:46,267 --> 00:20:52,033
You know, no matter how deep the
wound is in a person's heart,

340
00:20:52,100 --> 00:20:54,633
time will still heal it.

341
00:20:55,900 --> 00:21:01,667
And no matter where their life
decisions have taken them

342
00:21:01,733 --> 00:21:06,500
and no matter how much
their dreams

343
00:21:06,567 --> 00:21:08,867
and principles changed them,

344
00:21:08,967 --> 00:21:12,400
only one thing remains
unchanged.

345
00:21:13,333 --> 00:21:16,567
They are still good people.

346
00:21:16,633 --> 00:21:18,400
Agree or disagree?

347
00:21:18,467 --> 00:21:20,100
Left or right?

348
00:21:20,167 --> 00:21:22,933
- Right!
- Ouch, what's with you?

349
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,333
Sorry, Grandmother,
I was carried away.

350
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:27,033
Sorry, Grandmother.
I was carried away.

351
00:21:27,100 --> 00:21:29,467
You always mean
what you do to me.

352
00:21:29,533 --> 00:21:30,933
Can I say sorry?

353
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,033
Sorry...

354
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:33,200
be careful.

355
00:21:33,267 --> 00:21:34,900
- You have a lot of...
- Just pluck it.

356
00:21:34,967 --> 00:21:36,700
-What if I just color your hair?
-Just pluck it out.

357
00:21:36,767 --> 00:21:39,567
Just pluck it out. It's itchy.

358
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:42,367
Hey...

359
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:43,700
I'm careful.

360
00:21:43,767 --> 00:21:44,600
Hurry.
Here it is.

361
00:22:03,467 --> 00:22:04,467
Hey, Celeste.

362
00:22:08,967 --> 00:22:13,100
About the other day, I'm sorry
if I offended you

363
00:22:13,167 --> 00:22:15,100
when I said that I don't
have anything to do

364
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:17,500
with the Pili nut business.

365
00:22:17,567 --> 00:22:21,033
It's just that I'm under so much
pressure with Celestial.

366
00:22:21,100 --> 00:22:22,767
We understand, my Child.

367
00:22:24,533 --> 00:22:26,000
That's okay, Celeste.

368
00:22:26,067 --> 00:22:28,433
We have a lot of money
in Pili nuts.

369
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:30,567
And we don't have to share it

370
00:22:30,633 --> 00:22:32,700
with someone who has a bad
attitude like you.

371
00:22:32,767 --> 00:22:33,700
Sebastian!

372
00:22:35,033 --> 00:22:36,667
That's the truth.

373
00:22:36,733 --> 00:22:37,900
Why?

374
00:22:37,967 --> 00:22:40,033
Is she the only one
who can be honest here?

375
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:43,100
If she is very eager
to leave this house,

376
00:22:43,167 --> 00:22:47,900
well for me, I can't wait for
her to get out of our lives.

377
00:22:49,300 --> 00:22:51,367
I don't know
why you still believe

378
00:22:51,433 --> 00:22:53,867
that this person
will have a heart.

379
00:22:53,933 --> 00:22:56,633
Sebastian, stop it.

380
00:23:31,867 --> 00:23:33,233
Hey.

381
00:23:33,300 --> 00:23:35,067
You know you should watch
where you're going.

382
00:23:35,133 --> 00:23:36,700
Do you own this road?

383
00:23:36,767 --> 00:23:38,400
Why? Do you own this road?

384
00:23:38,467 --> 00:23:39,767
Do you have sapak
(problem in the head)?

385
00:23:39,833 --> 00:23:40,933
What's sapak ?

386
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:44,833
We want to promote our tradition
of making handicrafts.

387
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:49,233
We're happy you're here and
giving us a little attention.

388
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:50,733
I don't like this.

389
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,133
Maybe we should call your dad.

390
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:55,667
Mommy, please don't.

391
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:58,467
He will only ask me to go
to his mistress.

392
00:23:58,533 --> 00:23:59,567
He didn't just lift me up.

393
00:23:59,633 --> 00:24:02,633
He gave me wings to fly.

394
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:10,433
And so whatever I am now,
it's all because of Tonito.

395
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:12,467
I'm happy he came
into your life.

396
00:24:12,533 --> 00:24:13,933
I'm also happy
whatever you are now.

397
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:16,767
But no matter what you say,
no matter what you do.

398
00:24:16,833 --> 00:24:17,833
You're still good.

399
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:19,400
It's about Tonito.

400
00:24:19,467 --> 00:24:20,767
What about Tonito?

401
00:24:20,833 --> 00:24:22,167
I want him back.

402
00:24:22,233 --> 00:24:26,067
And I will do everything
that I can to win him back.

403
00:24:26,133 --> 00:24:28,867
Why do you think did Mikoy
bring you to familiar places?

404
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:31,567
Dear, of course,
it was assigned to him.

405
00:24:31,633 --> 00:24:34,333
I know you're naïve sometimes,
but you're not stupid.

406
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:35,667
He still likes you.

407
00:24:35,733 --> 00:24:39,033
If you ask me, maybe he
hasn't moved on from you.

408
00:24:39,100 --> 00:24:41,367
What's up between you
and that provincial boy?

409
00:24:41,433 --> 00:24:43,667
I just left you
for a moment yesterday

410
00:24:43,733 --> 00:24:45,267
and it looks like I was already
replaced.

411
00:24:45,333 --> 00:24:46,767
You come too strong
with the locals.

412
00:24:46,833 --> 00:24:49,633
Not a single word from you,
James.

413
00:24:49,700 --> 00:24:51,900
Let her enjoy it.

414
00:24:51,967 --> 00:24:53,533
That's her last.

415
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:56,633
Now that I'm back in your
company as a stakeholder,

416
00:24:56,700 --> 00:25:00,100
my world with Tonito
will become smaller.

417
00:25:00,167 --> 00:25:03,267
You deserve my brother's love,
Aurelia.

418
00:25:03,367 --> 00:25:05,300
But you should act right away.

419
00:25:05,367 --> 00:25:08,633
Mikoy can't come and he sent me
a replacement.

420
00:25:08,700 --> 00:25:12,533
We'll start at 9 am sharp
and finish at 5 pm sharp.

421
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:15,500
You have an hour for lunch
at 12 noon sharp,

422
00:25:15,567 --> 00:25:18,333
15-minute break at 3 pm sharp,

423
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:20,900
and 30 seconds water break
every hour.

424
00:25:20,967 --> 00:25:23,300
The phone is not allowed
at work.

425
00:25:23,367 --> 00:25:26,000
I'm planning to make a
recommendation to the Mayor

426
00:25:26,067 --> 00:25:28,300
to continue with the case
against her.

427
00:25:30,967 --> 00:25:32,600
What did cuz do this time?

428
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,233
It's huge.
